HEADWORD: Homogangliate
<hw>Ho`mo*gan"gli*ate</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[<ets>Homo-</ets> + <ets>gangliate</ets>.]</ety> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>Having the ganglia of the nervous system symmetrically arranged, as
in certain invertebrates; -- opposed to
<xex>heterogangliate</xex>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

